      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "I think you can get the best of both worlds by making the expiry logic have some randomness.\n\nFor example, the mempool janitor running exactly every 24 hrs means that an attacker can know when you'll expire a transaction (by doing some probing) and use it for new attacks, but even making that interval have a Â±1 hour variation completely removes that risk (without losing the roughly predictable expiration of transactions on the network overall).\n",
