      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I don't think the attacker needs to know. I think he can just try constantly to relay the replacement and nodes will take it when they take it, it just gives him an excuse to also flood the network.\n\nUnreliability in expiration will mean that you really ought to wait even longer in re-announcing. \n\nConsider:\n\nsend -> [has] -> [has] -> [has]\n           [has] - [has] - [!has]\n           [!has] - [has] - [!has]\nresend-> [has] -> [has] - [!has]\n            [has] - [!has] - [!has]\n\nBecause the resend was before everyone dropped the transaction, the middle node in that example rejected it on resend and didn't forward to the further node that had already dropped it.\n",
      "created_at" : "2014-02-27T17:12:35Z",
